quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  42,1,Ha Mim
  42,2,´Ayn Sin Qaf
  42,3,"That is how He sends revelation to you and those before you. Allah is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  42,4,"Everything in the heavens and everything in the earth belongs to Him. He is the Most High, the Magnificent"
  42,5,"The heavens are all but rent asunder from above when the angels glorify their Lord with praise and ask forgiveness for those who are on the earth. Allah is the Ever-Forgiving, the Most Merciful"
  42,6,"As for those who take others besides Him as protectors, Allah takes care of them. You are not set over them as a guardian"
  42,7,"Accordingly We have revealed to you an Arabic Qur´an so that you may warn the Mother of Cities* and those around it, and give warning of the Day of Gathering about which there is no doubt: one group in the Garden, the other in the Blazing Fire"
  42,8,"If Allah had willed, He would have made them a single nation. But He admits whoever He wills into His mercy and the wrongdoers have no protector and no helper"
  42,9,Have they then taken others besides Him as protectors? But Allah is the Protector. He gives life to the dead. He has power over all things
  42,10,"The judgement concerning anything you differ about is Allah´s concern. That is Allah, my Lord — I have put my trust in Him and to Him I turn —"